A man arrested in possession of R10-million worth of currency will be appearing at the Bellville Magistrate’s Court on Thursday. The 38-year-old was at the Cape Town International Airport on Wednesday. In a statement released by the Hawks, they said the suspect was allegedly from Pietermaritzburg ​en route to the United Arab Emirates. “Customs officials impounded just over R10-million worth of currency and the Hawks’ Serious Commercial Crime Unit members were summoned to the scene for further investigations,” the statement read. Provincial Head of the Hawks, Brigadier Neil Oliver said the probe in this will be to determine the trail and origin of the money. The suspect will be facing charges of failing to declare the cash and contravening the Customs and Exercise Act. TNA Reporter 